title: For Sale:  Thanks for your response scalperslayer@yahoo.com
postcontent:
Oddly enough, I am compelled to answer your email question with a reasoned response as opposed to a flame and a questioning of your manhood. You asked " should I flag them all or just a select few".. It's a legitimate question. Honestly , that's a decision that only you can make. While I share your outrage at the opportunistic gouging that has plagued the shooting community, I have sought  alternative sources for ammo and have not paid, and more importantly, sold, any ammo above pre panic prices. Are there assholes who line up at walmart at five am to clear the shelves and repost for sale two hours later at double the price?  Yes. Are there "those guys selling on this board? Yes. Am I as pissed as you? Yes.
However, I choose to behave in a rational manner and realize that there will always be gougers and  casting a broad net where you end up screwing  legitimate sellers is not the best course of action. Want to kill off the walmart trolls and restore rational pricing for 22lr, I will join your crusade as it  benefits me and the local shooting community. We have the same goals, but we chose to go about achieving them differently ...

Since I bought it in 2012, I have shot approximately 125 rounds (probably less than 30 of them were actually .375 magnum and the rest were .38 special) through the pistol. This handgun is regarded as one of the best made revolvers and has been featured in the AMC show The Walking Dead. It is the blued edition and features the 6" barrel and has an adjustable rear sight aperture. I have shot a number of revolvers and I am a firm believer in that this is by far the best revolver I have ever shot. I have been able to accurately shoot one inch targets from up to 25 yards away with ease and the action is absolutely excellent. I am selling this pistol because I recently moved to Chicago and I no longer have a need for it. Unfortunately the gun laws in Illinois are much more strict than Indiana and I don't really have the use to hold on to it anymore. Aesthetically the pistol is in excellent condition with a few scratches near the front of the barrel (probably from a holster from a previous owner). postcontent: The Tactical 20 was designed by Todd Kindler, owner of The Woodchuck Den, Inc. for precision long-range varmint shooting. The goal was to design a twenty-caliber cartridge with super long-range performance, but on a modest case design to minimize recoil and noise. Todd also selected the time proven and readily available top quality 223 case to base his Tactical 20 on (most shooters call it the 20 TAC today). Todd designed the 20 TAC with the accuracy proven 30-degree shoulder and the proper neck length to accommodate a wide range of bullets that he knew would be available down the road. The 20 TAC is one of the early twenty caliber cartridges that Todd has designed and it soon “blew the 20 caliber door wide open”! With 30 to 40 grain bullets, it is one of the most accurate and efficient 20 calibers available today. With the high B.C. 40 grain bullets, it has less bullet drop and wind drift than the 220 Swift! I offer a service which allows you to capture a snapshot of your inventory for record keeping purposes.   The information gathered on your collection can range from a single line record to multiple lines of detailed information of each firearm or accessory.   An example might be: Make, model, finish, serial number, caliber, purchase price, value price, custom work completed, etc.   

I take a photo of each firearm, compile a line item document, and produce you a record of all inventory in the form of a hard copy file, or can create a CD/DVD of your inventory.   

NOTE: I AM NOT affiliated with ANY agency, government organization, or force.  The data gathered for your collection will NOT be retained in any way, shape, or form.  

I have created several portfolios for many people as security against fire, flood, theft, or Trust allocations.   Generally, it's much easier to capture a snapshot of your investment and place a copy in your safe or safety deposit box than it is to buy a safe for every lot of investment.  

Precious metals, jewelry, automobiles, heirlooms, collectables can all be added to your record.   Depending on the portfolio request, I can provide the service and creation of document for a flat fee of $45.00

I travel to you, or meet in your specified location.

title: For Sale/Trade:  SCAM ALERT??? Update - definite scam!
postcontent:
I've had several people tell me that they have had the exact same email sent to them on different classified websites over the past year or so. 

I had a guy offer to buy my pistol, however, as he was impaired he could not recieve phone calls so he would call me sometime when he could. He wanted to send me a check for the asking price plus $50 for shipping. Then when I had the money he would call me to arrange collection. But first HE WANTED MY FULL NAME, ADDRESS AND PHONE NUMBER to mail me a check. 

If he has all my personal details he can just watch my house, call to check if I am home and rob me of my guns and valuables if he knows I am not there. All this while I am waiting for his check to arrive in the mail. Or maybe some other scam. 

Armslist email was - REDACTED
Second email came from - REDACTED

Pay for shipping then arrange to collect? Doesn't sound right to me. 

Full email below:

"Hello ,

Thanks for your reply concerning my inquiry. I am quite comfortable
with the condition and price of the item but due to the nature of my
health, I can not receive phone call as I am Impaired but i will call
you as soon as i can. I will be adding $50 to the purchase price for
the shipment... I want you to hold it for me before any other
interested person. Please provide your full name, Address and your
Phone number so that I can send your payment. I will be paying you by
Certified check. It will take 2 -3 days for the payment to get to
you...As for
delivery, I will make arrangements for the pick-up after you have
received payment, If this meets your approval, kindly get back to me,
as soon as possible, with your name, phone # and mailing address where
payment will be sent, so that I can make an arrangement on the Check.

Note: As soon as you have your money in hand, we can talk about the
picking up of the item. I would like you to take the posting off
Armslist.com today.You can send text or mail to my inbox , I will reply as soon
as I get it.
REDACTED
Best Regards,
Walker"

title: For Sale:  Star BM 9mm with 4 mags, box, papers

postcontent: This is a Star BM, imported by Interarms way-back-when. It is the compact model. It is an all steel Browning pistol design very much like the 1911A1 Colt we all love. The weight reduces felt recoil and adds to durability. Feel is very similar to a 1911. Among the differences, it lacks the grip safety and removeable backstrap. It breaks down for cleaning like a Colt. It comes in the original box with manual, paperwork and four magazines (not clips). I read on a Star sight that the Colt 3 1/2" holster is a good fit. It is an excellent pistol I've had for years. Google it for info.
